cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

This paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms to learn the topology and connection weights of a neural network that controls a robot or virtual agent. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper specifically focuses on the evolution of robot trajectories, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of mutations to create new pathways, which is a common technique in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for optimizing neural networks. The paper also discusses the complexity of evolved behavior, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the potential usefulness of the proposed methods, which suggests it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
